Learning Outcomes

After completing this course, the successful students will be able to:

describe how households’ utility maximization results in the demand curve and how firms’ profit maximization or cost minimization results in the supply curve;
analyze the market mechanism, in particular, the determination of the price for each good by utilizing both mathematical and graphical representations of demand and supply functions; and
discuss issues pertain to monopoly, externality, and government intervention by applying the main idea of the market mechanism.
